<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<em><strong>No spoilers here, please.</strong></em> <p>
<em><strong>NO SPOILERS HERE!</strong></em> 
</p>
<p>
Archers are to bows what warriors are to melee. They are the best class around with any bow, crossbow, or sling. 
</p>
<p>
Archers need a lot of ammunition. Early in the game, archers learn how to make ammo from junk found in the dungeons. They also gain, at skill level 20, the unique ability to make their arrows/bolts/shots pierce through monsters! 
</p>
<p>
Starting stat modifiers, starting Skills, innate abilities and starting equipment:  Please see the in-game help. 
</p>
<p>
Archers create ammo via the 'm' command. You need dungeon junk to make ammo. Each type of ammo requires certain kinds of junk. The first type of ammo you can make is pebbles; as you increase in skill you'll be able to make other types. 
</p>
<p>
Style note: Ammunition is commonly referred to in ToME discussion with ungrammatical but handy nomenclature: 'an ammo' (singular), and 'ammos' (plural). 'Ammo' (plural) is also used. 
</p>
